            maintenance window.</para>
MaintenanceTrackName.documentation: The name of the maintenance track that the cluster will change to during the next maintenance window.

EncryptionType.zonbookDocumentation: <para>The encryption type for a cluster. Possible values are: KMS and None. For the China region the possible values are None, and Legacy. </para>
EncryptionType.documentation: The encryption type for a cluster. Possible values are: KMS and None. For the China region the possible values are None, and Legacy.

PendingModifiedValues.zonbookDocumentation:
<simpara>A value that, if present, indicates that changes to the cluster are pending.
            Specific pending changes are identified by subelements.</simpara>
PendingModifiedValues.documentation: A value that, if present, indicates that changes to the cluster are pending. Specific pending changes are identified by subelements.

ClusterVersion.zonbookDocumentation: <simpara>The version ID of the Amazon Redshift engine that is running on the cluster.</simpara>
ClusterVersion.documentation: The version ID of the Amazon Redshift engine that is running on the cluster.

AllowVersionUpgrade.zonbookDocumentation: A Boolean value that, if true, indicates that major version upgrades will be applied automatically to the cluster during the maintenance window.
AllowVersionUpgrade.documentation: A Boolean value that, if true, indicates that major version upgrades will be applied automatically to the cluster during the maintenance window.

NumberOfNodes.zonbookDocumentation: <simpara>The number of compute nodes in the cluster.</simpara>
NumberOfNodes.documentation: The number of compute nodes in the cluster.

PubliclyAccessible.zonbookDocumentation: A Boolean value that, if true, indicates that the cluster can be accessed from a public network.
PubliclyAccessible.documentation: A Boolean value that, if true, indicates that the cluster can be accessed from a public network.

Encrypted.zonbookDocumentation: A Boolean value that, if true, indicates that data in the cluster is encrypted at rest.
Encrypted.documentation: A Boolean value that, if true, indicates that data in the cluster is encrypted at rest.

Status.zonbookDocumentation:
<simpara>The status of the restore action. Returns starting, restoring, completed, or
            failed.</simpara>
Status.documentation: The status of the restore action. Returns starting, restoring, completed, or failed.

CurrentRestoreRateInMegaBytesPerSecond.zonbookDocumentation:
<simpara>The number of megabytes per second being transferred from the backup storage.
            Returns the average rate for a completed backup.</simpara>
CurrentRestoreRateInMegaBytesPerSecond.documentation: The number of megabytes per second being transferred from the backup storage. Returns the average rate for a completed backup.

SnapshotSizeInMegaBytes.zonbookDocumentation: <simpara>The size of the set of snapshot data used to restore the cluster.</simpara>
SnapshotSizeInMegaBytes.documentation: The size of the set of snapshot data used to restore the cluster.

ProgressInMegaBytes.zonbookDocumentation: <simpara>The number of megabytes that have been transferred from snapshot storage.</simpara>
ProgressInMegaBytes.documentation: The number of megabytes that have been transferred from snapshot storage.

ElapsedTimeInSeconds.zonbookDocumentation:
<simpara>The amount of time an in-progress restore has been running, or the amount of time
            it took a completed restore to finish.</simpara>
ElapsedTimeInSeconds.documentation: The amount of time an in-progress restore has been running, or the amount of time it took a completed restore to finish.

EstimatedTimeToCompletionInSeconds.zonbookDocumentation:
<simpara>The estimate of the time remaining before the restore will complete. Returns 0 for
            a completed restore.</simpara>
EstimatedTimeToCompletionInSeconds.documentation: The estimate of the time remaining before the restore will complete. Returns 0 for a completed restore.

RestoreStatus.zonbookDocumentation:
<simpara>A value that describes the status of a cluster restore action. This parameter
            returns null if the cluster was not created by restoring a snapshot.</simpara>
RestoreStatus.documentation: A value that describes the status of a cluster restore action. This parameter returns null if the cluster was not created by restoring a snapshot.

Status.zonbookDocumentation: Describes the status of the cluster. While the transfer is in progress the status is transferringdata.
Status.documentation: Describes the status of the cluster. While the transfer is in progress the status is transferringdata.

CurrentRateInMegaBytesPerSecond.zonbookDocumentation: <para>Describes the data transfer rate in MB's per second.</para>
CurrentRateInMegaBytesPerSecond.documentation: Describes the data transfer rate in MB's per second.

TotalDataInMegaBytes.zonbookDocumentation: <para>Describes the total amount of data to be transfered in megabytes.</para>
TotalDataInMegaBytes.documentation: Describes the total amount of data to be transfered in megabytes.

DataTransferredInMegaBytes.zonbookDocumentation: <para>Describes the total amount of data that has been transfered in MB's.</para>
DataTransferredInMegaBytes.documentation: Describes the total amount of data that has been transfered in MB's.

EstimatedTimeToCompletionInSeconds.zonbookDocumentation: <para>Describes the estimated number of seconds remaining to complete the transfer.</para>
EstimatedTimeToCompletionInSeconds.documentation: Describes the estimated number of seconds remaining to complete the transfer.

ElapsedTimeInSeconds.zonbookDocumentation: <para>Describes the number of seconds that have elapsed during the data transfer.</para>

DataTransferProgress.documentation: Describes the status of a cluster while it is in the process of resizing with an incremental resize.

HsmClientCertificateIdentifier.zonbookDocumentation:
<simpara>Specifies the name of the HSM client certificate the Amazon Redshift cluster uses to
            retrieve the data encryption keys stored in an HSM.</simpara>
HsmClientCertificateIdentifier.documentation: Specifies the name of the HSM client certificate the Amazon Redshift cluster uses to retrieve the data encryption keys stored in an HSM.

HsmConfigurationIdentifier.zonbookDocumentation:
<simpara>Specifies the name of the HSM configuration that contains the information the
            Amazon Redshift cluster can use to retrieve and store keys in an HSM.</simpara>
HsmConfigurationIdentifier.documentation: Specifies the name of the HSM configuration that contains the information the Amazon Redshift cluster can use to retrieve and store keys in an HSM.

Status.zonbookDocumentation:
<simpara>Reports whether the Amazon Redshift cluster has finished applying any HSM settings
            changes specified in a modify cluster command.</simpara>
        <simpara>Values: active, applying</simpara>
Status.documentation:
Reports whether the Amazon Redshift cluster has finished applying any HSM settings changes specified in a modify cluster command.

Values: active, applying

HsmStatus.zonbookDocumentation:
<simpara>A value that reports whether the Amazon Redshift cluster has finished applying any
            hardware security module (HSM) settings changes specified in a modify cluster
            command.</simpara>
        <simpara>Values: active, applying</simpara>
HsmStatus.documentation:
A value that reports whether the Amazon Redshift cluster has finished applying any hardware security module (HSM) settings changes specified in a modify cluster command.

Values: active, applying

DestinationRegion.zonbookDocumentation:
<simpara>The destination region that snapshots are automatically copied to when cross-region
            snapshot copy is enabled.</simpara>
DestinationRegion.documentation: The destination region that snapshots are automatically copied to when cross-region snapshot copy is enabled.

RetentionPeriod.zonbookDocumentation:
<simpara>The number of days that automated snapshots are retained in the destination region
            after they are copied from a source region.</simpara>
RetentionPeriod.documentation: The number of days that automated snapshots are retained in the destination region after they are copied from a source region.

ManualSnapshotRetentionPeriod.zonbookDocumentation:
<para>The number of days that automated snapshots are retained in the destination region
            after they are copied from a source region. If the value is -1, the manual snapshot is retained indefinitely. </para>
        <para>The value must be either -1 or an integer between 1 and 3,653.</para>
ManualSnapshotRetentionPeriod.documentation:
The number of days that automated snapshots are retained in the destination region after they are copied from a source region. If the value is -1, the manual snapshot is retained indefinitely.

The value must be either -1 or an integer between 1 and 3,653.

SnapshotCopyGrantName.zonbookDocumentation: <simpara>The name of the snapshot copy grant.</simpara>
SnapshotCopyGrantName.documentation: The name of the snapshot copy grant.

ClusterSnapshotCopyStatus.zonbookDocumentation:
<simpara>A value that returns the destination region and retention period that are
            configured for cross-region snapshot copy.</simpara>
ClusterSnapshotCopyStatus.documentation: A value that returns the destination region and retention period that are configured for cross-region snapshot copy.

NodeRole.zonbookDocumentation: <simpara>Whether the node is a leader node or a compute node.</simpara>
NodeRole.documentation: Whether the node is a leader node or a compute node.

PublicIPAddress.zonbookDocumentation: <simpara>The public IP address of a node within a cluster.</simpara>

Tags.documentation: The list of tags for the cluster.

Key.documentation: The key, or name, for the resource tag.

members.zonbookDocumentation: <simpara>A tag consisting of a name/value pair for a resource.</simpara>
members.documentation: A tag consisting of a name/value pair for a resource.

KmsKeyId.zonbookDocumentation:
<simpara>The AWS Key Management Service (AWS KMS) key ID of the encryption key used to
            encrypt data in the cluster.</simpara>
KmsKeyId.documentation: The AWS Key Management Service (AWS KMS) key ID of the encryption key used to encrypt data in the cluster.

EnhancedVpcRouting.zonbookDocumentation: An option that specifies whether to create the cluster with enhanced VPC routing enabled. To create a cluster that uses enhanced VPC routing, the cluster must be in a VPC. For more information, see Enhanced VPC Routing in the Amazon Redshift Cluster Management Guide. If this option is true, enhanced VPC routing is enabled. Default: false
EnhancedVpcRouting.documentation:
An option that specifies whether to create the cluster with enhanced VPC routing enabled. To create a cluster that uses enhanced VPC routing, the cluster must be in a VPC. For more information, see Enhanced VPC Routing in the Amazon Redshift Cluster Management Guide.

If this option is true, enhanced VPC routing is enabled.

Default: false

IamRoles.zonbookDocumentation:
<simpara>A list of AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) roles that can be used by the
            cluster to access other AWS services.</simpara>
IamRoles.documentation: A list of AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) roles that can be used by the cluster to access other AWS services.

IamRoleArn.zonbookDocumentation: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the IAM role, for example, arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/RedshiftCopyUnload.
IamRoleArn.documentation: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the IAM role, for example, arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/RedshiftCopyUnload.

ApplyStatus.zonbookDocumentation: A value that describes the status of the IAM role's association with an Amazon Redshift cluster. The following are possible statuses and descriptions. in-sync: The role is available for use by the cluster. adding: The role is in the process of being associated with the cluster. removing: The role is in the process of being disassociated with the cluster.
ApplyStatus.documentation:
A value that describes the status of the IAM role's association with an Amazon Redshift cluster.

The following are possible statuses and descriptions.

  • in-sync: The role is available for use by the cluster.

  • adding: The role is in the process of being associated with the cluster.

  • removing: The role is in the process of being disassociated with the cluster.

members.zonbookDocumentation:

            Amazon Redshift cluster to access other AWS services.</simpara>
members.documentation: An AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) role that can be used by the associated Amazon Redshift cluster to access other AWS services.

PendingActions.documentation: Cluster operations that are waiting to be started.

        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
               <para>AllowCancelResize: a boolean value indicating if the resize operation can be cancelled.</para>

            <listitem>
               <para>ResizeType: Returns ClassicResize</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>

Returns the following:
